                        the United States Delegation at Paris</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v05p2</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d708</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">708</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-10-27T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-10-27T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="708" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d708">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/10–2648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss> at Paris</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-27T17:00:00-05:00">October 27, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 330. Assumption set forth third para.
                        <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 488, Oct. 26, is correct. Under
                    authority <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 266, Oct. 21 you should limit
                    your action to speaking very briefly in support of and voting for resolution
                    whose text was transmitted as <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 489.<note n="1" xml:id="d708fn1">Dated October 26, not printed; but see footnote 3,
                            <ref target="#pg_1519">p. 1519</ref>.</note> We suggest that last para.
                    this draft resolution might more appropriately repeat language of resolution
                    July 15, which referred to “further action under Chapter VII” rather than
                    specific reference to Art. 41.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
